# Repo-root build-context excludes. This is the SINGLE source for all four image
# builds whose compose context is the repo root: frontend (frontend/Dockerfile),
# docs (docs-site/Dockerfile), backend (backend/Dockerfile), and mcp
# (mcp/Dockerfile). It supersedes the former per-package .dockerignore files
# (backend, mcp, frontend, docs-site), which are deleted.
#
# Each Dockerfile selectively COPYs only what it needs (its own package + shared,
# plus the workspace metadata for the Python builds). This file keeps every
# context lean and, critically, keeps secrets (.env*) and rebuilt artifacts out.
#
# backend/, mcp/, and contract/ are NOT excluded: they are uv workspace members
# whose pyproject.toml the backend/mcp resolve layer must read. The side effect is
# that the frontend/docs contexts now also carry the Python packages; the
# venv/cache/test excludes below cap that, and those Dockerfiles COPY only their
# own dirs regardless.

# Rebuilt inside the image (JS toolchain)
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.vitepress/cache
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo
.turbo

# Rebuilt inside the image (Python toolchain) — backend/mcp now enter the context
**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.hypothesis
**/.coverage
**/.coverage.*
**/htmlcov
**/coverage.xml

# Tests never ship in an image
**/tests

# VCS, CI, and secrets (.env* keeps the committed .env.prod out of the context)
.git
.gitignore
.github
.env*

# Dirs no image build COPYs
e2e
skill
deployments
scripts
docs

# Root tooling and scratch
docker-compose*.yml
justfile
ruff.toml
.DS_Store
